HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1405
By Powell
A RESOLUTION to honor and celebrate the Spain Men's National
Team for selecting the State of Tennessee and
the City of Chattanooga to host its group phase
base camp and training site for the 2026 World
Cup.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to commend a global
sporting event that will contribute significantly to Tennessee's economy while entertaining
soccer fans worldwide; and
WHEREAS, the Spain Men's National Team will use the Baylor School's soccer complex
in Chattanooga as its team base camp and training site in preparation for the group phase of the
FIFA 2026 World Cup this summer; and
WHEREAS, additionally, the Spain's Men's National Team and members of the Real
Federación Española de Fútbol (RFEF) delegation will reside in downtown Chattanooga as the
squad prepares for the opening round of the World Cup; and
WHEREAS, RFEF ultimately selected Baylor as Spain's training site because of the
school's superior campus facilities and its infrastructure to support elite athletic performance;
and
WHEREAS, Baylor provides the necessary privacy and security for Spain to prepare for
the World Cup without distraction, and for logistical purposes, Chattanooga is a mere ninety
minutes from Atlanta, Georgia, where La Roja will play two of its group stage matches; and
WHEREAS, winning RFEF's approval for the Baylor School to serve as the Spain Men's
National Team base camp and training site required the hard work, collaboration, and vision of a
partnership that included Baylor, Vision Hospitality Group, Hamilton County, and the Sports and
Events Corporation; and
HJR1405
017734
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Baylor's selection is not only an honor, but it also solidifies Chattanooga's
reputation as a serious destination for fans of the beautiful game and extends its legacy as an
accomplished host of world-class soccer; and
WHEREAS, there is also an important economic component to Chattanooga hosting a
base camp and training site for Spain, the FIFA top-ranked team in the world and the favorite to
win the 2026 World Cup; and
WHEREAS, according to an analysis prepared for San Antonio, Texas's World Cup
planning by Market Edge, non-host U.S. cities serving as an official FIFA training hub are
projected to generate between $5 million and $15 million from a base camp arrangement; and
WHEREAS, the University of Tennessee will play an important role in the success of the
first World Cup held on American soil since 1994; and
WHEREAS, because of its renowned turfgrass management program, the University of
Tennessee was selected by FIFA to create the best natural grass playing surfaces at all sixteen
host cities and dozens of training facilities across the U.S., Canada, and Mexico; and
WHEREAS, it is indeed exciting that the world's greatest sporting event is being
contested on American soil this summer; it is equally exciting that the State of Tennessee, the
City of Chattanooga, and Hamilton County will play an important role in making the 2026 World
Cup an event to cherish and remember; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and celebrate La Roja, the Spain Men's National Team, and the
Real Federación Española de Fútbol for selecting the State of Tennessee and the City of
Chattanooga to host its group phase base camp and training site for the 2026 World Cup and
extend to them our warmest welcome to the Volunteer State and the Scenic City.
- 2 - 017734

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
